articles.author: David D. Kirkpatrick and Ronen Bergman
articles.title: Its Missiles Did Little Damage, but Iran Has More Potent Weapons
articles.description: Missiles, militants and hackers: Iran has an array of stealthier and more effective options if hostilities escalate.
articles.content:
The latest cycle of attacks between the United States and Iran started with a rocket attack that killed an American contractor in Iraq. The United States retaliated with a strike on an Iranian-backed militia, beginning a cycle of escalation.
